#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an5.39"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.39:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.39:0.2"
msgid "4. Sumanavagga "
msgstr "4. With Sumanā "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.39:0.3"
msgid "39. Puttasutta "
msgstr "39. A Child "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an5.39:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, ṭhānāni sampassantā mātāpitaro puttaṃ icchanti kule jāyamānaṃ. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, parents see five reasons to wish for the birth of a child in the family. "

msgctxt "an5.39:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni pañca? "
msgstr "What five? "

msgctxt "an5.39:1.3"
msgid "Bhato vā no bharissati; "
msgstr "Since we looked after them, they’ll look after us. "

msgctxt "an5.39:1.4"
msgid "kiccaṃ vā no karissati; "
msgstr "They’ll do their duty for us. "

# NOTE: At AN 7.52, etc. kulavamsa clearly means family tradition rather than family lineage.
msgctxt "an5.39:1.5"
msgid "kulavaṃso ciraṃ ṭhassati; "
msgstr "The family traditions will last. "

msgctxt "an5.39:1.6"
msgid "dāyajjaṃ paṭipajjissati; "
msgstr "They’ll take care of the inheritance. "

msgctxt "an5.39:1.7"
msgid "atha vā pana petānaṃ kālaṅkatānaṃ dakkhiṇaṃ anuppadassatīti. "
msgstr "Or else when we have passed away they’ll give an offering on our behalf. "

msgctxt "an5.39:1.8"
msgid "Imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañca ṭhānāni sampassantā mātāpitaro puttaṃ icchanti kule jāyamānanti. "
msgstr "Parents see these five reasons to wish for the birth of a child in the family. "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an5.39:2.1"
msgid "Pañca ṭhānāni sampassaṃ, "
msgstr "Seeing five reasons, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.39:2.2"
msgid "puttaṃ icchanti paṇḍitā; "
msgstr "astute people wish for a child. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.39:2.3"
msgid "Bhato vā no bharissati, "
msgstr "Since we looked after them, they’ll look after us. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.39:2.4"
msgid "kiccaṃ vā no karissati. "
msgstr "They’ll do their duty for us. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an5.39:3.1"
msgid "Kulavaṃso ciraṃ tiṭṭhe, "
msgstr "The family traditions will last. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.39:3.2"
msgid "dāyajjaṃ paṭipajjati; "
msgstr "They’ll take care of the inheritance. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.39:3.3"
msgid "Atha vā pana petānaṃ, "
msgstr "Or else when we have passed away "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.39:3.4"
msgid "dakkhiṇaṃ anuppadassati. "
msgstr "they’ll give an offering on our behalf. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an5.39:4.1"
msgid "Ṭhānānetāni sampassaṃ, "
msgstr "Seeing these five reasons "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.39:4.2"
msgid "puttaṃ icchanti paṇḍitā; "
msgstr "astute people wish for a child. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.39:4.3"
msgid "Tasmā santo sappurisā, "
msgstr "And so good people, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.39:4.4"
msgid "kataññū katavedino. "
msgstr "grateful and thankful, "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.44, sc5
msgctxt "an5.39:5.1"
msgid "Bharanti mātāpitaro, "
msgstr "look after their parents, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.39:5.2"
msgid "pubbe katamanussaraṃ; "
msgstr "remembering what was done for them in the past. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.39:5.3"
msgid "Karonti nesaṃ kiccāni, "
msgstr "They do for their parents, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.39:5.4"
msgid "yathā taṃ pubbakārinaṃ. "
msgstr "as their parents did for them in the past. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an5.39:6.1"
msgid "Ovādakārī bhataposī, "
msgstr "Following their advice, looking after those who raised them, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.39:6.2"
msgid "kulavaṃsaṃ ahāpayaṃ; "
msgstr "the family traditions are not lost. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.39:6.3"
msgid "Saddho sīlena sampanno, "
msgstr "Faithful, accomplished in ethics, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.39:6.4"
msgid "putto hoti pasaṃsiyo”ti. "
msgstr "such a child is praiseworthy.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.39:6.5"
msgid "Navamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
